I'm planning a refactor of weight-cache builders and weight-loading code across
the torch model tests. Don't write code — produce a plan.

**Goal:** Maximize shared infrastructure for weight loading and caching across
torch model tests, and ideally integrate it into the model tester base class so
per-model test code doesn't have to wire up caches by hand. Functions that are custom to each model can be added to the loader in tt-forge-models.

**Anchor files to study first:**
- `tests/torch/models/glm4_moe/build_weight_cache_glm.py` — GLM-4.7, BF16 on HF,
  single-pass HF → post-sparse build.
- `tests/torch/models/deepseek_v3_2_exp/build_weight_cache.py` — DeepSeek V3.1,
  FP8 with block-wise `weight_scale_inv`, two-pass HF → BF16 pre-sparse →
  stacked post-sparse.
- `tests/benchmark/test_llms.py` — currently open, likely loads weights.

